---
name: bankan
description: Read and mutate local kanban boards stored as markdown files. Use when the user asks about cards, lanes, boards, or tasks tracked in bankan.
---

## Basics

`{{.Cmd}}` manages local kanban boards stored as plain markdown files.
Board is auto-detected by walking up from cwd; use `--board <dir>` to target one explicitly.

## Typical agent workflow

1. `{{.Cmd}} lane list` — get exact lane names (case-sensitive).
2. `{{.Cmd}} card list` — get 5-char card IDs (e.g. `ab12c`).
3. Use IDs and exact lane names in subsequent commands.

## Lane

```
{{.Cmd}} lane list
{{.Cmd}} lane add <name>
{{.Cmd}} lane rename <old-name> <new-name>
{{.Cmd}} lane remove <name>               # lane must be empty
```

## Card

```
{{.Cmd}} card list [--lane <name>] [--label <id>] [--archived]
{{.Cmd}} card show <id>                   # title, body, labels, comments
{{.Cmd}} card add  --lane <name> --title "<title>" [--body "<body>"|--body -] [--label <id>]
{{.Cmd}} card edit <id> [--title "<t>"] [--body "<b>"|--body -] [--add-label <id>] [--remove-label <id>]
{{.Cmd}} card move <id> --lane <name>
{{.Cmd}} card archive <id>
{{.Cmd}} card restore <id> --lane <name>  # un-archive; destination lane required
{{.Cmd}} card delete  <id> [--force]      # omit --force to preview; --force to confirm
{{.Cmd}} card search  <id> [--root <dir>] [--include-archived] # find which board(s) contain a card by ID
```

## Comment

```
{{.Cmd}} comment list <card-id>                                    # also shows comment IDs
{{.Cmd}} comment add  <card-id> --text "<text>"|--text - [--author "<name>"]
{{.Cmd}} comment edit <comment-id> --card <card-id> --text "<text>"|--text -
```

## Label

```
{{.Cmd}} label list
{{.Cmd}} label add    --name "<name>" [--color "<hex>"]
{{.Cmd}} label edit   <id> [--name "<name>"] [--color "<hex>"]
{{.Cmd}} label remove <id>
```

## Board

```
{{.Cmd}} board show                              # name, created date, label summary
{{.Cmd}} board reorder --root <dir> <id1> ...   # set tab display order for all boards
{{.Cmd}} board hide   <id> --root <dir>          # hide board from tab bar (preserves content)
{{.Cmd}} board unhide <id> --root <dir>          # restore board to tab bar
```

`board reorder`, `board hide`, and `board unhide` require `--root`.

## Stdin input (IMPORTANT for agents)

Pass `-` as the value to read content from stdin until EOF — **always prefer this for multi-line bodies**:

    echo "# Heading\n\nBody text." | {{.Cmd}} card add --lane <name> --title "<t>" --body -
    echo "My comment"              | {{.Cmd}} comment add <card-id> --text -
    cat description.md             | {{.Cmd}} card edit <id> --body -

## Rules

- Lane names are **case-sensitive** — always read from `lane list` before use.
- `--label` (card add) and `--add-label`/`--remove-label` (card edit) take **label IDs**, not names — get IDs from `label list`.
- Archived cards are hidden from `card list` by default; use `--archived` to see them.
- `card delete` without `--force` only prints a preview — add `--force` to delete permanently.
- `card search` scans all active boards (including view boards) under `--root` (default: cwd); archived view boards are skipped by default — use `--include-archived` to include them. Archived cards within active boards are not searched. Prints a warning when the same ID appears in multiple boards.
